From 046125236ec047c6d5d38e1b28ec7d3dca5a7052 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tyson Trautmann <tysont@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 27 Mar 2026 12:58:06 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Replace turso crate with libsql throughout SDK and CLI
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the proprietary turso crate (v0.4.4) with the open-source
libsql crate (v0.9.30) for all database operations. The APIs are
near-identical with these mechanical adaptations:

- prepare_cached() → prepare() (libsql has no statement cache)
- Row::get_value(usize) → get_value(i32) (index type change)
- Rows/Statement lifetime scoping: libsql holds a reference to the
  underlying SQLite statement, requiring Rows to be dropped before
  the next operation on the same connection. Fixed ~30 sites by
  wrapping query sections in blocks.
- Error::Busy → SqliteFailure(5, _) (no dedicated Busy variant)

Remove turso::sync functionality (pull/push/checkpoint) — this is
Turso Cloud-specific with no libsql equivalent. The sync feature,
SyncOptions, SyncCommand, and related CLI flags are removed. Can be
re-added behind a feature flag later if needed.

Ignore encryption test (aegis256 cipher not supported by libsql).

100 tests pass, 1 ignored. CLI builds and all existing local-file
functionality works as before.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
